  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing the Profitability of Livestock Production for Improved Livelihoods</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LWR is working with l&#x2019;Union Potal Saabirrina, an umbrella organization comprised of 15 community groups, to improve livestock feeding as a means to increase the net annual incomes of agropastoralist households by at least 50% through improved profitability of 
animal production.

610 agropastoralists, including 172 women, from 10 member villages of the Union will directly benefit from the project.

The project represents a first phase of support to 
animal production in Bittou zone which will focus on improving animal feeding, revitalizing milk production and animal fattening practices and improving milk 
processing.  

Objective #1:  Increase milk production by 100% and the weight of cattle by at least 50% during the dry 
season by improving the application of animal husbandry techniques among members of the Bittou 
Union of Breeders
 
Objective #2:  Increase the profitability of livestock production by enhancing the organizational technical and financial capacity of the cooperative members of Bittou Union of Breeders</narrative>
  </description>
